      "content": {
        "title": "Tibia and Fibula Shaft Fractures — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Diaphyseal fractures of the tibia and fibula including open injuries with compartment syndrome risk.",
        "summary": "Tibia is subcutaneous with high open fracture rate. Intramedullary nailing is preferred for closed diaphyseal fractures when soft tissues allow."
      },
